{"id":488,"category_slug":"english-conversations","category_name":"Conversations","position":89,"title":"89. How have you been?","subtitle":"","level":"B1","parts":21,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/english-conversations/89-how-have-you-been.488/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/89-how-have-you-been-2022-03-07-21-34-59/0-89-how-have-you-been.mp3","transcript":"Raymond!\nOh, hi, Grace! How have you been?\nGood! I hear you've been to Toronto for a few days.\nYes. I just got back yesterday.\nDid you have a nice visit?\nReally nice. It was very good going around downtown and shopping.\nAnd I saw the Toronto Blue Jays game at Skydome.\nIt seems that Toronto is a very exciting city.\nMy brother Stanley was there, too.\nYou've met Stanley, haven't you?\nSure. I met him when he was here in Hamilton last year.\nWhat's he doing these days? Still teaching baseball?\nYes, as a matter of fact, he just began to teach elementary school.\nGreat. How's everything with his kids?\nHave you met my nieces?\nYes, they visited you once in the summer, didn't they?\nRight. They're both fine.\nI haven't seen them in a long time. They must be really big.\nWell, they will come over this Christmas.\nLet's have a great Christmas party together.\nThat's a good idea.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:49:07","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Raymond!","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/89-how-have-you-been-2022-03-07-21-34-59/1.mp3","time_start":2.35,"time_end":3.33},{"position":2,"content":"Oh, hi, Grace! How have you been?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/89-how-have-you-been-2022-03-07-21-34-59/2.mp3","time_start":3.67,"time_end":5.95},{"position":3,"content":"Good! I hear you've been to Toronto for a few days.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/89-how-have-you-been-2022-03-07-21-34-59/3.mp3","time_s